Robert Blake's murder trial revolves around his desire to keep the baby he had with his slain wife, Bonny Lee Bakley.
Witnesses testified to his anxiety over Bakley's pregnancy and his wish to separate from her but retain custody of the child.
Prosecutors argued that Blake orchestrated his wife's murder after failed attempts to hire others.
Defense attorney Schwartzbach dismissed the allegations as absurd, questioning the credibility of witnesses.
The trial, filled with twists and turns, sheds light on the complex and bizarre world of a former TV detective accused of a heinous crime.
